<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-11-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="158" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d158">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-11-22"><hi rend="italic">November 22,
                                    1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Conger requests to be informed whether the United States will
                            continue to accept payments in silver or whether the same treatment
                            accorded to other powers, in case the proposal of the Chinese Government
                            is accepted, will be insisted upon.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>